data.description: It’s your lucky day! Back on the market. This beauty is the charmer of Charles street. It is very unassuming from the road, but once you start your tour, you will be enchanted. The pride of ownership shines on all three finished levels, as does all the natural lighting. The home owners have taken such wonderful care and have made many upgrades over the years, to include: a new main water and sewer line, indoor water meter(laundry room), patio: re-screening, new fan and painted, new garage door on the oversized detached garage, all new black top on the upper and lower parking areas, 25 year warranty roof and gutters were installed in 2017, carpet in upstairs bedrooms and carpet/padding in the basement, sunroom-carpet, tile and fans, custom blinds in the dining room/first floor office (or bedroom) , Merrimac wood stove with fan, new chimney lining and cap, and custom floating shelves in the expansive sunroom. The kitchen has been updated with Samsung stainless steel appliances, subway tile backsplash and granite counter tops.  Samsung washer and dryer were installed in 2020. NO HOA,   Easy commuter range to NAS PAX River, Joint Base Bolling, Joint Base Andrews, NSWC Indian Head, NSWC Dahlgren, multiple access routes to Wash D.C. Beltway and VA. Small town size with mid-size city amenities: close to wide range of restaurants, shopping, walking distance to The University of Maryland Charles Regional Medical Center, walking/biking trails to nearby park/lake. Easy access to recreation areas; fishing, hunting, and boating on the Potomac. A home you do not want to miss out on!
